Romeo Crennel was fired as coach of
the  Kansas City Chiefs  after a National Football League-worst
2-14 season.  Crennel took over last season when Todd Haley was fired.
This season, he was at the scene as linebacker Jovan Belcher
committed suicide after killing his girlfriend.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
